      "amount": "1/4 tsp",
      "notes": "whole spices, freshly grated"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Line a 9x13-inch baking dish with parchment paper.",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together fish stock, olive oil, garlic, lemon juice, salt, black pepper, cinnamon, and allspice.",
    "Add the cauliflower to the bowl and toss to coat with the fish stock mixture.",
    "Arrange the cod fillets in a single layer on the prepared baking dish.",
    "Top each cod fillet with a spoonful of the cauliflower mixture and a dollop of Greek yogurt.",
    "Cover the dish with aluminum foil and bake for 20 minutes.",
    "Remove the foil and continue baking for an additional 10-12 minutes, or until the fish is cooked through and the cauliflower is tender.",
    "Garnish with chopped parsley and serve hot."
  ],
